First Read: 03-Mar-26
SB337 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to school lands; to add Section 16-20-10 to
5 the Code of Alabama 1975, to require the Department of
6 Conservation and Natural Resource, upon request of the
7 relevant local board of education, to issue a deed to certain
8 school indemnity lands to the board.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
10 Section 1. Section 16-20-10 is added to the Code of
11 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
12 §16-20-10
13 (a) It is the intent of the Legislature that this
14 section effectuates and carries out its intent in passing
15 Section 30-5.20 of the Constitution of 2022 during the 2024
16 Regular Session which was ratified in November of 2024
17 pursuant to a statewide election.
18 (b) Upon the request of the Franklin County Board of
19 Education, the Department of Conservation and Natural
20 Resources shall issue to the board a deed to all indemnity
21 lands located in Walker and Fayette counties for which schools
22 in Franklin County are the sole beneficiary.
23 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
24 1, 2026.
